- 'on-time' refers to a schedule status where the actual arrival/departure time matches the scheduled time; 
- halt duration is calculated in seconds by subtracting the start time '00:00:00' from the halt time; 
- the time frame is limited to the month of October 2023, from the 1st to the 31st.

sql:
SELECT train_name
FROM trains
WHERE capacity > 400;

SELECT COUNT(train_id) AS total_daily_trains
FROM route_trains
WHERE frequency = 'daily' AND route_id = 0;

SELECT train_name 
FROM trains 
WHERE train_id = 1;

SELECT train_name, operator
FROM trains
ORDER BY train_name ASC;

